  "prompt": "How much are 4 tons of gold worth?",
  "response": "To calculate the value of 4 tons of gold, you'll first need to know the current price of gold per ounce, as gold is typically priced in ounces. As of my last update, the price of gold can fluctuate significantly and can be checked from various financial news sources.\n\n1 ton is equivalent to 2,000 pounds, and there are 16 ounces in a pound. Therefore, 1 ton of gold equals:\n\n\\[ \n2,000 \\text{ pounds} \\times 16 \\text{ ounces/pound} = 32,000 \\text{ ounces}\n\\]\n\nSo, 4 tons of gold would equal:\n\n\\[ \n4 \\text{ tons} \\times 32,000 \\text{ ounces/ton} = 128,000 \\text{ ounces}\n\\]\n\nNow, if you know the current price of gold per ounce, you can multiply that price by 128,000 ounces to get the total value.\n\nFor example, if gold is priced at $1,900 per ounce, the calculation would be:\n\n\\[ \n128,000 \\text{ ounces} \\times 1,900 \\text{ dollars/ounce} = 243,200,000 \\text{ dollars}\n\\]\n\nTo get an accurate estimate, check the current gold price and perform the calculation accordingly.",
